It's weird though, 'cos I tend to be on the visual side of stuff, like when I remember things I have to have SEEN it or visualised it, or I don't remember it (if someone tells me something, I forget, they write it down &amp; show it to me, BAM! I remember). But when I'm drawing it's different, it's like I'm kinda feeling around in 3D, in my head, and it just kinda turns up on paper, I hardly &quot;visualise&quot; it at all. *shrugs* I'd like to know how a lot of people &quot;think&quot; when they're drawing, especially good people. Not to emulate, 'cos I think I know how to do it, (I just need more practice...a LOT more practice!!) but it'd just be kinda interesting. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.buttonpusher.net/kindamanga">KINDAMANGA!</a> <BR>
